The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for solving complex control tasks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of imitation learning and reinforcement learning algorithms suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the focus on robotics benchmark tasks suggests that it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics). The use of value functions and policies suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control), while the mention of simulations suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
